## 24.2 Header `<iterator>` synopsis [iterator.synopsis] ## {#iterator.synopsis}

Modify the synopsis as follows:
<pre>
// [...]
namespace std {
  // [...]
  // [alg.req.ind.cmp], concept indirectly_comparable
  template&lt;class I1, class I2, class R, class P1 = identity, class P2 = identity&gt;
  concept indirectly_comparable = <i>see below</i>; // freestanding

  <ins>// [alg.req.searchable], concept searchable
  template&lt;class Searcher, class I, class S, class P = identity&gt;
  concept searchable = <i>see below</i>; // freestanding</ins>

  // [alg.req.permutable], concept permutable
  template&lt;class I&gt;
  concept permutable = <i>see below</i>; // freestanding
  // [...]
}
</pre>

<i>Editor's Note: Insert the following subclause between 24.3.7.5 Concept `indirectly_comparable` [alg.req.ind.cmp] and 24.3.7.6 Concept `permutable` [alg.req.permutable]</i>

## 24.3.7.� Concept `searchable` [alg.req.searchable] ## {#alg.req.searchable}

1. The `searchable` concept specifies the requirements of algorithms that interact with searchers (22.10.18 [func.search]) to search for a sequence in another sequence.

```cpp
template<class Searcher, class I, class S, class P = identity>
  concept searchable =
    copyable<Searcher> &&
    invocable<Searcher, I, S, P> &&
    ranges::forward_range<invoke_result_t<Searcher, I, S, P>>
```

## 26.4 Header `<algorithm>` synopsis [algorithm.syn] ## {#algorithm.syn}

Modify the synopsis as follows:
<pre>
// [...]
namespace std {
  // [...]
  // [alg.contains], contains
  namespace ranges {
    // [...]
    template&lt;<i>execution-policy</i> Ep, <i>sized-random-access-range</i> R1, <i>sized-random-access-range</i> R2,
             class Pred = ranges::equal_to, class Proj1 = identity, class Proj2 = identity&gt;
      requires indirectly_comparable&lt;iterator_t&lt;R1&gt;, iterator_t&lt;R2&gt;, Pred, Proj1, Proj2&gt;
      bool contains_subrange(Ep&amp;&amp; exec, R1&amp;&amp; r1, R2&amp;&amp; r2, Pred pred = {}, Proj1 proj1 = {},
                             Proj2 proj2 = {}); // freestanding-deleted

    <ins>template&lt;forward_iterator I, sentinel_for&lt;I&gt; S,
             class Searcher, class Proj = identity&gt;
      requires searchable&lt;Searcher, I, S, Proj&gt;
      constexpr bool contains_subrange(I first, S last,
                                       const Searcher&amp; searcher, Proj proj = {});
    template&lt;forward_range R, class Searcher, class Proj = identity&gt;
      requires searchable&lt;Searcher, iterator_t&lt;R&gt;, sentinel_t&lt;R&gt;, Proj&gt;
      constexpr bool contains_subrange(R&amp;&amp; r, const Searcher&amp; searcher, Proj proj = {});</ins>
  }
  // [...]
  // [alg.search], search
  // [...]
  template&lt;class ForwardIterator, class Searcher&gt;
    constexpr ForwardIterator
      search(ForwardIterator first, ForwardIterator last, const Searcher&amp; searcher);

  <ins>namespace ranges {
    template&lt;forward_iterator I, sentinel_for&lt;I&gt; S,
             class Searcher, class Proj = identity&gt;
      requires searchable&lt;Searcher, I, S, Proj&gt;
      constexpr auto search(I first, S last,
                            const Searcher&amp; searcher, Proj proj = {});
    template&lt;forward_range R, class Searcher, class Proj = identity&gt;
      requires searchable&lt;Searcher, iterator_t&lt;R&gt;, sentinel_t&lt;R&gt;, Proj&gt;
      constexpr auto search(R&amp;&amp; r, const Searcher&amp; searcher, Proj proj = {});
  }
  </ins>
  // [...]
}
</pre>

## 26.6.4 Contains [alg.contains] ## {#alg.contains}

Add to the end of this clause:

```cpp
template<forward_iterator I, sentinel_for<I> S,
         class Searcher, class Proj = identity>
  requires searchable<Searcher, I, S, Proj>
  constexpr bool ranges::contains_subrange(I first, S last,
                                           const Searcher& searcher, Proj proj = {});
```

5. *Returns*:

```cpp
!ranges::empty(ranges::search(first, last, searcher, move(proj)))
```

```cpp
template<forward_range R, class Searcher, class Proj = identity>
  requires searchable<Searcher, iterator_t<R>, sentinel_t<R>, Proj>
  constexpr bool ranges::contains_subrange(R&& r, const Searcher& searcher, Proj proj = {});
```

6. *Returns*:

```cpp
!ranges::empty(ranges::search(forward<R>(r), searcher, move(proj)))
```

## 26.6.15 Search [alg.search] ## {#alg.search}

Add to the end of this clause:

```cpp
template<forward_iterator I, sentinel_for<I> S,
         class Searcher, class Proj = identity>
  requires searchable<Searcher, I, S, Proj>
  constexpr auto ranges::search(I first, S last,
                                const Searcher& searcher, Proj proj = {});
```

13. *Effects*: Equivalent to: `return searcher(first, last, move(proj));`

```cpp
template<forward_range R, class Searcher, class Proj = identity>
  requires searchable<Searcher, iterator_t<R>, sentinel_t<R>, Proj>
  constexpr auto ranges::search(R&& r, const Searcher& searcher, Proj proj = {});
```

14. *Effects*: Equivalent to:

- `return searcher(forward<R>(r), move(proj))` if that expression is well-formed.
- Otherwise, `return searcher(ranges::begin(r), ranges::end(r), move(proj));`.

